modules.description: Provides functions to manage process creation, signal handling, and inter-process communication using Unix system calls. Operates on file descriptors, process identifiers, and signal codes. Enables spawning child processes for executing external commands and monitoring their execution status.

Provides functions to distribute work across multiple child processes, using a job manager to control execution. Operates on lists, arrays, and custom job structures, with results marshaled back to the master process. Enables parallel processing of independent tasks, such as batch data transformation or parallel computation, with control over concurrency and error handling.
